DCT:2013-03-22
George Lowe, the last surviving member of the team which first conquered Everest in 1953, died in Ripley on Wednesday after a long-term illness, with his wife Mary by his side. The last British climbing member of the 1953 team, Mike Westmacott, died last June. Before retiring in 1984, Mr Lowe worked as an Inspector of Schools with the Department of Education and Sciences, and he leaves three sons from a previous marriage.